<plot>A man has a dream where he travels the world to view various hardships brought upon the working class by capitalism: Children on treadmills, an uninsured horse being shot by it's owner, an elegant dinner party being overrun by socialists, and all of Manhattan ablaze. The film's use of striking visual allegories and it's Socialist point of view make it a rare American production of the time.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?655947</url></doc>
